The paper discusses a markup language for knowledge representation and data analysis, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of formal context and concept lattice aligns with the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which deals with knowledge representation and reasoning. The incorporation of information flow principles suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The use of ontologies and metadata aligns with the sub-category of language and grammar (cs.LG), while the focus on markup languages and data structuring suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
